 region pairs :- a region pair consists of two azure region in the same geography that are linked 
 together for disaster recovery purposes .
 benefits :- disaster recovery
            business contunity 
            data replication 
            improved reliability 
    e.g. :-  if one region becomes unavailable , services can continue from the paired region .

 availability ZONES :- available zones are physically separated locations  within an azure region .
    each availability zone has :- independent power 
                                  independent cooling 
                                  independent networking 
if one zone fails another will continue runnning .
it protects against data center failures . 
benefits :- high availability
            fault tolerance 
            disaster recovery support

 availability sets :- 
 availability sets are used to protect virtual machines from hardware failures  and maintainence events . 

 azure distributes VMS across different :- fault domain , update domain .

fault domain :- protect against hardware failures .
e.g. if one server rack fails , other VMs remain available .

update domain :- protects against planned maintainence . 
e.g. :- when azure updates one host , not all VMS are restart at the same time .

benefits :- improved VM availability 
            reduced downtime 
            protection from hardware and maintainence issues 

    availability sets are mainely used for VMs .

       availability zone                                     vs                     availability sets 
       @ different physical locations                             @same region 
       @protects against data center failures                     @ protect against hardware / update failure 
       @works across zones                                        @ works across fault /update domains 
       @ higher availability                                      @ VM - level availability.
